ENTRY            A0893   20260206   20260508   20260508       A132
SUBENT        A0893001   20260206   20260508   20260508       A132
BIB                 10         23
TITLE      The new element 112
AUTHOR     (S.Hofmann, V.Ninov, F.P.Hesberger, P.Armbruster,
           H.Folger, G.Muenzenberg,H.J.Schoett, A.G.Popeko,
           A.V.Yeremin, S.Saro, R.Janik, M.Leino)
REFERENCE  (J,ZP/A,354,229,1996)
INSTITUTE  (2GERGSI,4ZZZDUB,3SLKUB,2SF JYV)
FACILITY   (LINAC,2GERGSI) The UNILAC accelerator and
           the velocity filter SHIP (Separator for Heavy-Ion
           reaction Products) at GSI.
SAMPLE     (82-PB-208,ENR=0.990) The targets were prepared by
           deposition of a 450 ug/cm2 thick layer of 208Pb,
           enrichment 99.0% on 50-ug/cm2 thick carbon foils. The
           lead was covered by 15 ug/cm2 carbon.
DETECTOR   (MAGSP) The evaporated residues (ERs) were separated
           from the beam by the velocity filter SHIP and
           implanted into a position-sensitive strip Si detector
            (focal-plane stop detector)
           (SISD)
METHOD     (TOF)
STATUS     (TABLE,,S.Hofmann+,J,ZP/A,354,229,1996).Value from the
           Abstract.
HISTORY    (20110816C) SB
           (20260206U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              23
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           26
SUBENT        A0893002   20260206   20260508   20260508       A132
BIB                  4          6
REACTION   (82-PB-208(30-ZN-70,N)112-CN-277,,SIG)
DECAY-DATA (112-CN-277,0.240MSEC,A,11649.,,A,11454.)
           Alpha decay error is +-0.02 MeV (measured)
           Half-life error is +0.430/-0.090 msec (measured)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
HISTORY    (20260206U) SD: ERR-ANALYS updated. COMMENT deleted.
ENDBIB               6
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 4          1
EN         DATA       +DATA-ERR  -DATA-ERR
MEV        PB         PB         PB
344.       1.0        1.8        0.4
